OL,6,F"There's an attitude of 'it's happened
OL,7,Fnow, so there's no point in litigating
OL,8,Fpast arguments.' But after the 1979
OL,9,Freferendum, when Wales rejected
OL,10,Fdevolution, that didn't stop those in
OL,11,Ffavour of devolution and independence
OL,12,Ffrom making their case`and they won 20
OL,13,Fyears later."
OL,15,F"Just because something is hard
OL,16,Fdoesn't mean it's not possible`just
OL,17,Fask Nigel Farage and Brexit."
OL,19,FThe Conservatives have never won power
OL,20,Fin the Senedd, so, is this just a case
OL,21,Fof sour grapes?
