OL,6,F"It isn't Conservative policy," he
OL,7,Ftells Sharp End, saying the party
OL,8,Fshouldn't become "devo-sceptic". "Our
OL,9,Fpolicy is to make devolution work for
OL,10,Fthe people of Wales."
OL,12,FConservative Party hopeful Kemi
OL,13,FBadenoch has voiced devo-sceptic
OL,14,Fviews, while her rival for the crown,
OL,15,FRobert Jenrick, says the devolution
OL,16,Fsettlement is established.
OL,18,FIn 25 years of devolution, most of the
OL,19,Felectorate has never cast a vote.
